Part 1 - Fitting Models

For each of the following, construct a model for the relationship between x and y. Write a summary of your model, including:

  • a scatterplot containing both the data and the model curve;
  • one or more plots of the model residuals, along with a written assessment of these plots;
  • reasons for your choice of model;
  • your model equation, including the fitted parameter values;
  • interpretation of all model parameters in the context of the given variables;
  • a summary paragraph assessing the model and what it tells you about the relationship between x and y.
